1
00:00:18,813 --> 00:00:20,438
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:25,188
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:27,313 --> 00:00:28,938
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:31,147 --> 00:00:33,063
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:35,313 --> 00:00:37,147
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:38,938 --> 00:00:41,998
(Jirong / Kim Namsu, Mr. Kim / Song Wonsu, Chairman Lee /
Choi Sanghak) (Officer Sin / Im Changseop, Mina / Heo Yeseul)

7
00:00:42,022 --> 00:00:46,438
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 4)

8
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:48,688
(Hachi has run away from home)

9
00:00:53,022 --> 00:00:54,605
Is that all?

10
00:00:57,980 --> 00:00:59,647
Hey! Hurry up!

11
00:01:36,647 --> 00:01:37,980
Hurry! Come on!

12
00:01:38,730 --> 00:01:40,130
The quicker you finish
the quicker you get paid.

13
00:01:51,813 --> 00:01:53,730
This feels weird.

14
00:01:55,022 --> 00:01:56,438
What kind of weird?

15
00:01:57,480 --> 00:02:02,230
It feels like when my parents
used to bathe me when I was a kid.

16
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:04,897
You have memories like that?

17
00:02:06,563 --> 00:02:08,980
No, it's just a feeling.

18
00:02:09,105 --> 00:02:11,855
My memories of my
parents are already so blurry.

19
00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:16,022
I can barely recall them.

20
00:02:16,147 --> 00:02:18,438
The doctor said it was
because of that trauma.

21
00:02:18,563 --> 00:02:20,480
A part of my memory is gone.

22
00:02:22,230 --> 00:02:23,772
I see...

23
00:02:24,772 --> 00:02:26,452
I don't have memories of my mother either.

24
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,022
Why?

25
00:02:28,147 --> 00:02:29,563
I hatched from an egg.

26
00:02:29,688 --> 00:02:31,855
So the first thing I saw
when I was born was my dad.

27
00:02:32,272 --> 00:02:35,188
Wow... your amnesia is on another level.

28
00:02:35,313 --> 00:02:36,772
You're not even scrubbing properly.

29
00:02:36,897 --> 00:02:38,230
Turn around.

30
00:02:40,688 --> 00:02:45,772
Seriously, that's not how
we do it on my planet...

31
00:02:45,897 --> 00:02:47,105
Shut up.

32
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:03,438
This feeling... it's so nice.

33
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:32,123
That bakery owner right now...

34
00:03:32,147 --> 00:03:33,980
Is he the son of that
guy from 15 years ago?

35
00:03:35,522 --> 00:03:37,897
I don't know, I don't know anything.

36
00:03:38,022 --> 00:03:41,313
You say you don't know.
But you've been living here for 100 years.

37
00:03:41,438 --> 00:03:43,730
There was indeed a
bakery here 15 years ago.

38
00:03:43,855 --> 00:03:46,230
Their bread was really
popular around here back then.

39
00:03:46,355 --> 00:03:49,188
Business was booming before the incident.

40
00:03:49,313 --> 00:03:52,647
I didn't know you were
such a jerk back then.

41
00:03:52,772 --> 00:03:55,480
Hey, you were part of it too, okay?

42
00:03:55,605 --> 00:03:56,938
We built that building together.

43
00:03:57,063 --> 00:04:00,438
I just wanted to go back home.

44
00:04:00,563 --> 00:04:02,730
Yeah, exactly.

45
00:04:02,855 --> 00:04:05,063
You guys go back to your home.

46
00:04:05,188 --> 00:04:08,355
And I'll go make money and become
the richest person in the universe.

47
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,748
That was our deal from the start.

48
00:04:09,772 --> 00:04:13,105
The blueprint you brought
was completely wrong, wasn't it?

49
00:04:13,522 --> 00:04:15,272
That wasn't my fault!

50
00:04:17,397 --> 00:04:20,397
Fine, even if there was
a mistake back then.

51
00:04:20,522 --> 00:04:22,688
Let's just review the
issues from that time.

52
00:04:25,980 --> 00:04:28,063
This is the revised blueprint.

53
00:04:28,980 --> 00:04:31,605
Come on, take another look at this.

54
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:35,063
You better show me what
you're really capable of this time.

55
00:04:48,230 --> 00:04:50,647
Is my baby hungry?
Do you want something to eat?

56
00:04:57,897 --> 00:05:00,438
You scared me! What are you doing?

57
00:05:00,563 --> 00:05:03,563
That looks delicious, can I have some?

58
00:05:04,355 --> 00:05:06,730
I'm kidding! This is dog food, you know?

59
00:05:19,688 --> 00:05:20,688
(Basic Dog Food)

60
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,772
I like this one!

61
00:05:28,397 --> 00:05:29,797
You look so seductive wearing that.

62
00:05:31,063 --> 00:05:31,772
Where did you buy this?

63
00:05:31,897 --> 00:05:33,956
There's a convenience store
nearby, they sell them there.

64
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:35,563
Seeing you even wearing dog clothes...

65
00:05:35,688 --> 00:05:37,105
You must really like dogs, right?

66
00:05:37,230 --> 00:05:38,313
Do you have a dog?

67
00:05:45,647 --> 00:05:47,272
- Officer Shin.
- Yes.

68
00:05:48,438 --> 00:05:49,980
That's enough.

69
00:05:50,105 --> 00:05:51,563
Let her go.

70
00:05:51,681 --> 00:05:52,890
I wanted to stay here myself.

71
00:05:53,022 --> 00:05:54,063
Please, leave me alone.

72
00:05:54,188 --> 00:05:56,855
Ugh, whatever. Suit yourself.

73
00:05:56,980 --> 00:05:57,980
I'm off the clock.

74
00:05:58,022 --> 00:05:59,022
Okay.

75
00:06:00,647 --> 00:06:02,855
Alright, let's go over this again.

76
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:05,897
So why did you go to that bakery?

77
00:06:06,022 --> 00:06:08,480
Because I'm an influencer.

78
00:06:08,605 --> 00:06:13,105
I visit every new shop that opens.

79
00:06:13,230 --> 00:06:15,188
It's my responsibility to
inform my subscribers.

80
00:06:15,313 --> 00:06:16,593
So you were there to promote it?

81
00:06:16,647 --> 00:06:18,647
Oh, right... yeah, promotion.

82
00:06:18,772 --> 00:06:20,188
But I didn't expect...

83
00:06:20,313 --> 00:06:22,688
To get bitten by that dog-thing.

84
00:06:22,813 --> 00:06:24,355
That's how I ended up like this.

85
00:06:24,605 --> 00:06:26,605
Are there vicious dogs there?

86
00:06:26,730 --> 00:06:29,813
No, it's not a dog.

87
00:06:29,938 --> 00:06:32,772
It's this... this pervert
wearing a dog mask.

88
00:06:34,063 --> 00:06:36,438
And did he say anything else?

89
00:06:36,563 --> 00:06:39,522
Just stuff like it's a
bakery run by aliens.

90
00:06:39,647 --> 00:06:41,438
I just posted a thumbnail for now.

91
00:06:41,563 --> 00:06:42,897
That's the one.

92
00:06:43,022 --> 00:06:44,331
That perverted jerk in the dog mask.

93
00:06:44,355 --> 00:06:46,105
No, that person...

94
00:06:47,022 --> 00:06:48,522
Must be an alien.

95
00:06:48,772 --> 00:06:49,772
Is... is that so?

96
00:06:49,855 --> 00:06:52,813
But the person who kidnapped
me was someone else.

97
00:06:52,938 --> 00:06:55,522
He bit your finger, that's assault, right?

98
00:06:55,647 --> 00:06:57,355
Let's arrest him and investigate.

99
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,605
When?

100
00:06:58,730 --> 00:06:59,897
Now.

101
00:07:16,897 --> 00:07:18,081
Are we arresting him directly?

102
00:07:18,105 --> 00:07:19,105
Of course not.

103
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:22,605
We wait until he meets with other aliens
and catch him red-handed.

104
00:07:22,730 --> 00:07:23,897
Follow him.

105
00:07:34,563 --> 00:07:35,397
Look over there.

106
00:07:35,522 --> 00:07:37,272
I told you that dog-thing was suspicious.

107
00:07:40,938 --> 00:07:42,980
Hi, little doggy!

108
00:07:43,938 --> 00:07:47,563
Are you doing fine here? I'll see you... later...

109
00:07:51,188 --> 00:07:52,272
Customer.

110
00:07:52,397 --> 00:07:54,230
Is there something you're looking for?

111
00:07:54,348 --> 00:07:55,824
This one! I'm looking for this one!

112
00:07:55,855 --> 00:07:56,895
Oh, so you're a foreigner.

113
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:58,772
You need to pay first.

114
00:07:58,897 --> 00:08:00,355
Here, take it!

115
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,522
Boss, that's dog food!

116
00:08:04,647 --> 00:08:06,355
You'll get sick if you eat that.

117
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:07,855
I told you, you can't eat that!

118
00:08:07,980 --> 00:08:09,022
You can't eat this!

119
00:08:09,147 --> 00:08:10,397
You'll really get into trouble.

120
00:08:13,313 --> 00:08:14,772
Gotcha!

121
00:08:16,647 --> 00:08:18,147
What are you guys doing?

122
00:08:21,647 --> 00:08:23,063
Got this one too!

123
00:08:23,522 --> 00:08:25,688
Oh yeah, jackpot!

124
00:08:25,813 --> 00:08:27,355
What is this!?

125
00:08:27,938 --> 00:08:29,480
(Wooju Bakery)

126
00:08:50,147 --> 00:08:51,313
Um...

127
00:08:52,063 --> 00:08:55,105
Raon, are you asleep?

128
00:08:55,688 --> 00:08:58,563
No, I'm not.

129
00:08:58,938 --> 00:09:00,813
There's something I want to ask you...

130
00:09:01,730 --> 00:09:02,730
Yeah, go ahead.

131
00:09:02,813 --> 00:09:08,480
Woo-hyuk and... that princess... uh...

132
00:09:08,605 --> 00:09:09,938
Do they really get along?

133
00:09:13,772 --> 00:09:15,730
We get along pretty well too, don't we?

134
00:09:17,605 --> 00:09:19,188
I'm such a fool for asking you!

135
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:27,438
Boss, come in quickly!

136
00:09:28,688 --> 00:09:29,980
What?

137
00:09:32,355 --> 00:09:33,605
Hachi has dissapeared.

138
00:09:33,730 --> 00:09:35,397
Hachi really dissapeared!

139
00:09:35,522 --> 00:09:36,647
For real?

140
00:09:36,772 --> 00:09:37,772
Hachi is really missing?

141
00:09:37,855 --> 00:09:38,688
Yeah.

142
00:09:38,813 --> 00:09:42,022
Answer me, what is your relationship?

143
00:09:42,147 --> 00:09:45,397
How many times do I have to say it?
We met for the first time today.

144
00:09:45,522 --> 00:09:48,397
He's just a customer who came to
our convenience store to buy something.

145
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:50,605
You bit this person, didn't you?

146
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:52,605
That constitutes assault.

147
00:09:54,313 --> 00:09:58,022
You dare look at me? You bit
my finger and made it look like this!

148
00:09:58,147 --> 00:10:00,188
Looks like we'll be
investigating all night.

149
00:10:00,313 --> 00:10:03,647
Can a police officer just drag innocent
people in for questioning like this?

150
00:10:03,772 --> 00:10:07,522
Aliens must follow Earth's
laws when they come here.

151
00:10:07,647 --> 00:10:09,772
Stop talking so much.

152
00:10:09,897 --> 00:10:12,522
W-what, aliens?

153
00:10:12,647 --> 00:10:15,938
Officer, what are you doing?
Let me go!

154
00:10:16,063 --> 00:10:18,081
We don't even have a part-timer now,
the store is a mess.

155
00:10:18,105 --> 00:10:21,855
Wait a second. We're going
to do an alien identification test.

156
00:10:22,397 --> 00:10:26,897
Aliens who have been on Earth for a long
time are hard to distinguish from humans.

157
00:10:27,022 --> 00:10:30,897
The easiest way is a blood test.

158
00:10:31,022 --> 00:10:32,397
Let's start with a blood test.

159
00:10:32,522 --> 00:10:35,438
Right, let's check your
body temperature first.

160
00:10:36,105 --> 00:10:37,897
Are you really a police officer?

161
00:10:38,022 --> 00:10:40,272
Are you going to draw blood
from innocent people now?

162
00:10:41,397 --> 00:10:42,397
Hachi!

163
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,813
Come out!

164
00:10:44,438 --> 00:10:45,605
Hachi!

165
00:10:45,730 --> 00:10:47,147
Come here.

166
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:49,272
Hachi!

167
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,105
Hachi!

168
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:57,230
Come out!

169
00:10:59,022 --> 00:11:00,147
Hachi!

170
00:11:00,272 --> 00:11:01,480
Come out.

171
00:11:22,605 --> 00:11:24,039
Please, no blood please.

172
00:11:24,064 --> 00:11:25,981
I'm scared of blood please, no blood...

173
00:11:26,105 --> 00:11:27,664
There should be a thermometer
in the warehouse over there.

174
00:11:27,688 --> 00:11:29,528
There should be a
breathalyzer or thermometer.

175
00:11:29,605 --> 00:11:32,147
Wait, this person looks like a foreigner.
Is this really okay?

176
00:11:32,272 --> 00:11:34,188
Which country are you from?

177
00:11:34,213 --> 00:11:35,955
I came from a country far away from here.

178
00:11:35,980 --> 00:11:37,355
See, see!

179
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:39,563
He said he's from very far away.

180
00:11:39,688 --> 00:11:41,873
No way, the South Korean police
are treating a foreign tourist like this?

181
00:11:41,897 --> 00:11:43,397
Isn't this illegal?

182
00:11:43,522 --> 00:11:45,022
Watch them for me for a second.

183
00:11:45,147 --> 00:11:46,022
I'm going to get the thermometer.

184
00:11:46,147 --> 00:11:47,313
Okay.

185
00:11:49,813 --> 00:11:51,893
Do you think the handcuffs
will just open like that?

186
00:11:51,938 --> 00:11:54,480
You bit my finger, so
you have to pay the price.

187
00:11:54,605 --> 00:11:56,147
What on earth are you doing?

188
00:12:03,605 --> 00:12:05,730
So you're a magician.

189
00:12:05,855 --> 00:12:08,730
Wait... Officer! This guy is getting away!

190
00:12:08,855 --> 00:12:10,563
Hey! How are we supposed to find him?

191
00:12:13,147 --> 00:12:14,647
Officer! Hey!

192
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,890
Catch him! Hurry up and catch him!

193
00:12:19,022 --> 00:12:21,063
Catch him!

194
00:12:32,730 --> 00:12:35,105
It's so late, where could
that dog have gone?

195
00:12:35,647 --> 00:12:37,272
This has never happened before...

196
00:12:38,147 --> 00:12:41,438
Hey, when was the last time you saw Hachi?

197
00:12:42,397 --> 00:12:46,438
I don't know, he was just DJing all night.

198
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:52,900
Searching aimlessly
like this is so inefficient.

199
00:12:55,522 --> 00:12:57,563
Think about what that dog might like.

200
00:12:57,681 --> 00:12:59,640
Not a dog, it's Hachi!

201
00:12:59,772 --> 00:13:01,230
He's not a dog.

202
00:13:01,605 --> 00:13:03,063
But...

203
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:08,188
He seems to like what dogs like.

204
00:13:11,897 --> 00:13:13,297
Should we split up to look for him?

205
00:13:13,397 --> 00:13:17,355
What? You aren't thinking of...

206
00:13:21,230 --> 00:13:25,480
Colluding with that dog to
make a run for it, are you?

207
00:13:25,605 --> 00:13:27,230
Absolutely not!

208
00:13:27,355 --> 00:13:29,105
You stay right by my side, got it?

209
00:13:29,230 --> 00:13:31,272
I mean what I say.

210
00:13:31,397 --> 00:13:32,938
A prince should follow the rules.

211
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:35,355
A prince? Stop talking nonsense.

212
00:13:36,813 --> 00:13:38,313
Don't you dare leave my side!

213
00:13:38,431 --> 00:13:39,491
OK OK.

214
00:13:39,522 --> 00:13:44,605
I'm going this way, you
guys go that way. OK?

215
00:13:46,355 --> 00:13:47,855
I am a noble prince, after all.

216
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:49,730
I won't run away until I find Hachi.

217
00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:51,855
Let's go together!

218
00:13:52,647 --> 00:13:54,188
Officer Shin.

219
00:13:54,313 --> 00:13:55,647
What about the suspect?

220
00:13:56,563 --> 00:13:58,647
I'm heading back to
the station, wait for me.

221
00:13:58,772 --> 00:13:59,897
Got it.

222
00:14:01,730 --> 00:14:02,855
What kind of suspect is it?

223
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:05,230
The guy in the dog suit.
The one from Wooju Bakery.

224
00:14:05,355 --> 00:14:08,230
I've got the other one tied up
tight, he's not going anywhere.

225
00:14:08,355 --> 00:14:09,688
Understood.

226
00:14:13,855 --> 00:14:15,688
Sorry, let me untie you right away.

227
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:21,670
You catch them and then just let them go?
One escaped, and you let the other one loose.

228
00:14:22,688 --> 00:14:25,272
The South Korean police
are truly something else.

229
00:14:25,938 --> 00:14:27,730
What were the blood test results?

230
00:14:28,313 --> 00:14:31,188
It's B positive.

231
00:14:31,813 --> 00:14:33,480
So, is he an alien?

232
00:14:34,563 --> 00:14:35,313
No.

233
00:14:35,438 --> 00:14:38,438
If you dare mention the word
'alien' in front of me again...

234
00:14:38,563 --> 00:14:39,563
But, senior, however...

235
00:14:39,688 --> 00:14:41,272
You're still...!

236
00:14:41,397 --> 00:14:46,397
They didn't just handcuff
me, they taped my mouth shut!

237
00:14:46,563 --> 00:14:50,563
Isn't that a human rights
violation and torture?

238
00:14:50,855 --> 00:14:53,688
Sir, we are truly sorry. We
don't even know what to say.

239
00:14:53,813 --> 00:14:57,105
Enough! I'm going to report everything
you've done to the news stations.

240
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:59,350
Do the South Korean police
have nothing better to do?

241
00:14:59,438 --> 00:15:00,772
Playing some kind of alien game?

242
00:15:00,897 --> 00:15:03,105
It was truly our mistake,
we are very sorry.

243
00:15:03,230 --> 00:15:07,313
But sir, that companion
who came with you...

244
00:15:07,438 --> 00:15:08,438
Do you know him?

245
00:15:08,522 --> 00:15:12,688
No. He was just a foreign customer who came
to our convenience store to buy something.

246
00:15:12,813 --> 00:15:15,063
But he did look a bit like a magician.

247
00:15:17,272 --> 00:15:20,897
That guy isn't a magician, he's indeed an alien.

248
00:15:21,605 --> 00:15:24,647
An alien from a planet far, far away.

249
00:15:24,772 --> 00:15:25,980
An alien?

250
00:15:34,772 --> 00:15:37,355
Alright, everyone go home.

251
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:40,897
Just pretend today never happened.

252
00:15:41,022 --> 00:15:42,313
Bye.

253
00:15:45,063 --> 00:15:46,188
Wait...

254
00:15:50,230 --> 00:15:52,480
No, seriously, what exactly is that gun?

255
00:15:52,605 --> 00:15:53,813
This?

256
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:57,813
It's probably hard to understand
using Earth's scientific knowledge.

257
00:15:57,938 --> 00:15:59,855
Earth's scientific knowledge?

258
00:16:01,813 --> 00:16:03,230
Don't worry.

259
00:16:04,813 --> 00:16:06,480
I won't shoot you.

260
00:16:10,105 --> 00:16:13,272
Is he still at the police station?

261
00:16:13,397 --> 00:16:15,522
He was there a moment ago, but he escaped.

262
00:16:15,647 --> 00:16:17,313
We're looking for him now, too.

263
00:16:17,438 --> 00:16:18,772
No.

264
00:16:18,897 --> 00:16:20,105
We have to find him quickly.

265
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:22,897
Because... he's a foreigner.

266
00:16:23,022 --> 00:16:24,206
He doesn't speak the language well.

267
00:16:24,230 --> 00:16:25,480
Don't worry too much.

268
00:16:25,605 --> 00:16:26,938
We'll find him soon.

269
00:16:27,063 --> 00:16:28,938
I'll help look for him too.

270
00:16:29,063 --> 00:16:31,147
Oh, okay...

271
00:16:32,063 --> 00:16:33,188
Thanksz.

272
00:16:35,647 --> 00:16:37,147
We have to find him first.

273
00:16:37,272 --> 00:16:40,022
Otherwise, if he gets caught
again, they'll dissect him.

274
00:16:40,147 --> 00:16:43,355
Hey, why would the police dissect you?

275
00:16:43,813 --> 00:16:44,605
You're not frogs.

276
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:51,272
That's been a rumor where
we're from for a long time.

277
00:16:52,938 --> 00:16:54,438
You're actually buying into that?

278
00:16:55,022 --> 00:16:56,813
Were you raised in a bamboo forest?

279
00:16:58,272 --> 00:17:01,147
No wonder you believe such nonsense!

280
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:04,897
A bamboo forest? What's that...

281
00:17:07,230 --> 00:17:08,605
Let's go!

282
00:17:17,022 --> 00:17:17,855
What is that?

283
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:19,188
What?

284
00:17:22,897 --> 00:17:24,022
That's a playground, right?

285
00:17:24,647 --> 00:17:27,897
A playground? What's that for?

286
00:17:28,022 --> 00:17:31,022
It's a place for kids to play.

287
00:17:31,313 --> 00:17:35,105
What? What backwater place were you raised in
that you don't even know what a playground is?

288
00:17:35,563 --> 00:17:37,480
Want to play here for a bit before we go?

289
00:17:40,188 --> 00:17:45,147
This is my first time seeing a playground.

290
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:46,605
When I was little,

291
00:17:48,938 --> 00:17:50,418
I always wanted to play with friends.

292
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:52,147
That was my wish.

293
00:17:57,897 --> 00:17:59,230
I'm sorry.

294
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:05,063
But, you and I aren't friends, are we?

295
00:18:05,188 --> 00:18:07,730
Do you want to play with me?

296
00:18:07,855 --> 00:18:10,563
I'm your employer, your boss!

297
00:18:12,605 --> 00:18:13,605
I know, I know.

298
00:18:14,438 --> 00:18:16,063
Can't a boss be friends with me?

299
00:18:19,397 --> 00:18:25,022
Your eyes... they look like
the Earth I saw from space.

300
00:18:29,105 --> 00:18:30,355
W-what?

301
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:31,855
They're beautiful.

302
00:18:33,938 --> 00:18:35,355
Stop that!

303
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:41,605
You're a weirdo.

304
00:18:41,730 --> 00:18:45,647
Fine, I'll play with you for a bit.

305
00:18:45,772 --> 00:18:47,492
Since it's your first time at a playground,

306
00:18:48,313 --> 00:18:50,938
and you don't have any friends,
I'll keep you company, okay?

307
00:18:51,063 --> 00:18:52,480
Have you ever been on a slide?

308
00:19:23,647 --> 00:19:25,522
Wait for me!

309
00:19:41,938 --> 00:19:44,022
You really can't read the room, can you?

310
00:19:44,147 --> 00:19:46,605
The mood is perfect,
why go and interrupt them?

311
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:50,938
We still have to tell him.

312
00:19:52,938 --> 00:19:54,772
He looks like he's having a great time.

313
00:19:54,897 --> 00:19:56,147
Our Wooju,

314
00:19:56,272 --> 00:19:58,730
he's actually really worried, isn't he?

315
00:20:00,147 --> 00:20:02,313
Does that look like he's worried?

316
00:20:03,022 --> 00:20:06,188
He looks like he's having a blast to me.

317
00:20:06,313 --> 00:20:08,397
How long are you going to
keep worrying about him?

318
00:20:24,063 --> 00:20:25,647
Woo-hoo!

319
00:20:28,397 --> 00:20:31,397
Oh, merciful and great gods,

320
00:20:31,522 --> 00:20:33,938
I am your loyal follower.

321
00:20:34,063 --> 00:20:38,022
Oh, for heaven's sake...

322
00:20:38,147 --> 00:20:39,730
Vice President Oh!

323
00:20:40,647 --> 00:20:42,022
God bless us.

324
00:20:42,438 --> 00:20:46,272
Are you praying for us?

325
00:20:47,688 --> 00:20:50,730
It seems the gods of
Earth are truly powerful.

326
00:20:50,855 --> 00:20:53,063
Look, they both got released, didn't they?

327
00:20:53,188 --> 00:20:55,105
That was Chairman Lee who let them go.

328
00:20:55,230 --> 00:20:57,230
Chairman Lee isn't a god.

329
00:20:57,355 --> 00:20:59,105
Alright, enough of that.

330
00:21:00,647 --> 00:21:05,438
But do we really have to
do what Chairman Lee said?

331
00:21:05,563 --> 00:21:07,980
We'll be punished by the gods
of Earth if we do bad things.

332
00:21:08,105 --> 00:21:08,938
Vice President Oh,

333
00:21:09,063 --> 00:21:12,188
this is the only way we can get back home.

334
00:21:12,313 --> 00:21:13,605
You're right.

335
00:21:15,563 --> 00:21:16,105
These two...

336
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:17,289
they don't understand anything.

337
00:21:17,313 --> 00:21:19,397
It's not like there's no other way.
